title: AFRICA - Tanzania - Gogo Ritual Music

This is a straight field recording of some ritual music 
of the Gogo tribe in Tanzania. All selections are vocal-based, 
some solo, some choral, some a cappella, some with 
accompaniment. The vocal styles range from pretty melodic pieces 
to more ecstatic. This is more of an ethnographic document than 
a commercial release, but excellent in that capacity. 
~ Sean Westergaard
